  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Calcium scoring of the coronary arteries is use as a predictor of coronary stenosis. The aim
      of this study is to measure the calcium scoring of the abdominal aorta using an helicoidal
      fast scan and to correlate this measurement with classical cardiovascular risk factors and
      newer parameters reflecting vascular rigidity, like pulse velocity measurement.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
